verses.roman:
nā jāni rādhāra preme āche kata bala
ye bale āmāre kare sarvadā vihvala

synonyms: nā jāni—I do not know; rādhāra—of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī; preme—in the love; āche—there is; kata—how much; bala—strength; ye—which; bale—strength; āmāre—Me; kare—makes; sarvadā—always; vihvala—overwhelmed.
translation: "I do not know the strength of Rādhā's love, with which She always overwhelms Me.
